latestPosts.caption:
my Goa reccomendations🌴⬇️

Keep a day for exploring Panjim, Goa and visit Fontainhas 🎀, these are latin quarters housing colorful and pinteresty portuguese style villas with rich history behind them. 
you cant miss the -
* quaint cafes/ bakeries like Cafe Morango 
* vintage thrift stores like Bento Miguel Fernandes & Filhos Ltd. 
* Immaculate Conception Church (dress modest for this one, else your entry will be restricted)

North Goa beaches (less crowded) 🌊
* Vagator beach (perfect sundowner beach with a lot of cafe/clubs)
* Morjim beach (russian beach)
* Ashwem beach
( go to Baga beach for water activities tho, almost every activity is available there including kayaking) 

Sundowner cafe’s / restaurants ☀️
* Thalassa beach resort and restaurant,Ashwem (serves THE BEST PASTA EVER! do i really need to say more?)
* Dubki ,Vagator (beautiful sundowner place and vibey club at the night, i went there twice so that speaks for the food and the vibe!) 
* La Cucina, Morjim (authentic lowkey Italian restaurant) 
* The Place, Morjim (The Place has a completely different vibe than any other cafes/restaurants I visited in Goa, really popular among foreigners in the upper North Goa) 

Flea markets 🛍️
* Anjuna flea market (wednesdays till sunset) 
* Goa collective bazar (fridays  sunset to 1am in the night) 

Hope this helps! 🐚🩷
